1
00:00:20,888 --> 00:00:22,290
[Bell ringing]

2
00:00:26,894 --> 00:00:29,797
[Crowd noise]

3
00:02:06,894 --> 00:02:09,297
Get up.

4
00:02:09,397 --> 00:02:11,499
Get up.

5
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:12,300
Get up!

6
00:02:31,385 --> 00:02:34,288
[Machine gun fire]

7
00:02:37,391 --> 00:02:38,292
[Explosion]

8
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,783
[Crowd jeering]

9
00:03:43,324 --> 00:03:44,292
MAN IN CROWD: Get up!
Get up!

10
00:03:44,392 --> 00:03:45,092
Get up!

11
00:03:55,869 --> 00:03:58,939
I own you, kid.

12
00:03:59,039 --> 00:04:00,608
Do you have any
idea how much money

13
00:04:00,708 --> 00:04:04,312
You've cost me because
you've decided to give up?

14
00:04:04,412 --> 00:04:06,179
I'm sorry, Mr. Regetti.

15
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:08,048
You're havin' those
bad dreams again, right?

16
00:04:11,985 --> 00:04:13,421
I kept seeing her in that ring.

17
00:04:13,521 --> 00:04:14,221
Shh.

18
00:04:14,322 --> 00:04:15,723
Shh.

19
00:04:15,823 --> 00:04:19,026
She wasn't in the ring.

20
00:04:19,126 --> 00:04:20,528
But you don't understand.

21
00:04:20,628 --> 00:04:24,598
You had him beat!

22
00:04:24,698 --> 00:04:27,134
Learn to listen to
me more carefully,

23
00:04:27,234 --> 00:04:30,304
Or you're not going
to listen at all.

24
00:04:30,404 --> 00:04:32,239
I'll tell you what.

25
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:36,677
After you heal up, I want
you to come and visit me.

26
00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:38,946
I'm going to give you
another fight in the ring.

27
00:04:41,749 --> 00:04:44,184
I can't fight no
more, Mr. Regetti.

28
00:04:44,284 --> 00:04:46,620
Well, I can't fight no more.

29
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,955
Shh shh.
It's OK.

30
00:04:48,055 --> 00:04:49,557
It's OK.
You sit down.

31
00:04:49,657 --> 00:04:50,558
It's all right, baby.

32
00:04:50,658 --> 00:04:51,559
Hey, boys.

33
00:04:51,659 --> 00:04:53,961
It's OK.

34
00:04:54,061 --> 00:04:55,696
I'm gonna leave now.

35
00:05:03,704 --> 00:05:06,039
DR. MAY: I don't
have answers, Cajun.

36
00:05:09,843 --> 00:05:11,845
Maybe I could stay here
for a little while longer.

37
00:05:11,945 --> 00:05:13,013
DR. MAY: A month
is all you needed.

38
00:05:13,113 --> 00:05:15,115
And tomorrow that time is up.

39
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:27,628
But there ain't
nothing changed.

40
00:05:27,728 --> 00:05:29,262
Well, the only way you
can solve this problem

41
00:05:29,363 --> 00:05:31,732
Is to be on the outside.

42
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:34,167
You could make it out
there, and you know it.

43
00:05:34,267 --> 00:05:36,103
All you have to do is
put your past to sleep.

44
00:05:42,910 --> 00:05:45,646
They're still looking
for me out there.

45
00:05:45,746 --> 00:05:49,650
You have friends, a
job, a place to stay.

46
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:52,386
It's more than most vets.

47
00:05:52,486 --> 00:05:55,489
Life is a very precious
commodity, Cage.

48
00:05:55,589 --> 00:05:56,890
What we try to
accomplish here is

49
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:59,927
To replace negatives with hope.

50
00:06:00,027 --> 00:06:02,095
Oh, you'll do fine.

51
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:03,263
You'll get a job.

52
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:04,432
You have a very nice
friend in that young lady

53
00:06:04,532 --> 00:06:06,400
Who's coming to pick you up.

54
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:07,435
And you'll get well.

55
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:13,106
Be happy, Cage.

56
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:16,877
Just be happy, being alive.

57
00:06:16,977 --> 00:06:19,480
I must go.

58
00:06:19,580 --> 00:06:22,215
Doc.

59
00:06:22,315 --> 00:06:24,317
You can come back
to visit anytime

60
00:06:24,418 --> 00:06:25,953
That you feel closed in.

61
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:28,088
And besides, we have a
session scheduled in a month.

62
00:06:28,188 --> 00:06:29,990
So I can come back
and stay anytime if I...

63
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:30,791
No.

64
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:32,826
Visit.

65
00:06:32,926 --> 00:06:34,528
Come and see your friends,
have a session with me,

66
00:06:34,628 --> 00:06:36,997
And then go home.

67
00:06:37,097 --> 00:06:38,331
I'm scared, damn it.

68
00:06:42,470 --> 00:06:43,571
Why don't you go
and say goodbye

69
00:06:43,671 --> 00:06:45,539
To Legs before your friend
comes to pick you up?

70
00:06:48,576 --> 00:06:52,212
Because he never
comes to visit me.

71
00:06:52,312 --> 00:06:53,981
Why don't you just go down
there and bring him up

72
00:06:54,081 --> 00:06:55,449
So we can say goodbye?

73
00:06:55,549 --> 00:06:56,416
Can't do that just yet.

74
00:06:56,517 --> 00:06:59,319
His condition keeps
him in his room.

75
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,054
But I'm sure he'd like
to see you before you go,

76
00:07:01,154 --> 00:07:01,855
Don't you think?

77
00:07:04,858 --> 00:07:06,159
Yeah.

78
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:08,529
Yeah, sure.

79
00:07:08,629 --> 00:07:10,330
I'll see you in a month.

80
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,398
Take care of yourself.

81
00:07:11,499 --> 00:07:12,199
OK?

82
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:21,642
[Guitar playing]

83
00:07:52,339 --> 00:07:53,073
I thought you went home.

84
00:07:57,811 --> 00:08:00,147
Without saying goodbye
to my old buddy?

85
00:08:00,247 --> 00:08:02,816
No way.

86
00:08:02,916 --> 00:08:04,251
Figured you forgot.

87
00:08:13,594 --> 00:08:15,462
Say, Legs.

88
00:08:15,563 --> 00:08:17,164
You dress up just
to see me off, boy?

89
00:08:21,902 --> 00:08:24,938
Now, I can't very well just
jaunt on outside, now can I?

90
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:50,731
What's this?

91
00:08:50,831 --> 00:08:54,067
It's your going away gift.

92
00:08:54,167 --> 00:08:55,569
I can't take your guitar, man.

93
00:08:55,669 --> 00:08:59,039
I want you to have it.

94
00:08:59,139 --> 00:09:02,009
It's twisted out there, Cage.

95
00:09:02,109 --> 00:09:04,477
Downright scary.

96
00:09:04,578 --> 00:09:05,646
Hey, but when you
get out of here,

97
00:09:05,746 --> 00:09:07,247
You can take this guitar, and...

98
00:09:07,347 --> 00:09:08,315
No.

99
00:09:08,415 --> 00:09:10,784
I won't be leaving
here for a long time.

100
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:11,619
No way.

101
00:09:11,719 --> 00:09:14,554
Besides, I got another guitar.

102
00:09:14,655 --> 00:09:16,023
That means so much tension.

103
00:09:35,142 --> 00:09:38,478
Would you tell me just what
it is that keeps you here?

104
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:39,279
I got agoraphobia.

105
00:09:42,215 --> 00:09:43,416
There's no cure.

106
00:09:46,687 --> 00:09:49,322
Maybe I can help you.

107
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:51,859
I don't... I don't
need your help, dude.

108
00:09:51,959 --> 00:09:53,326
I'm... I'm fine.

109
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:56,063
I'll make a deal with you.

110
00:09:56,163 --> 00:09:57,530
What?

111
00:09:57,631 --> 00:10:00,934
If I can make it out
there, on the outside,

112
00:10:01,034 --> 00:10:02,469
You'll come visit me?

113
00:10:02,569 --> 00:10:05,272
I can't do it.

114
00:10:05,372 --> 00:10:06,406
I like it here.

115
00:10:12,913 --> 00:10:14,815
Well, do you plan on staying
in here the rest of your life?

116
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:17,417
I've tried.

117
00:10:17,517 --> 00:10:18,318
You think I haven't tried?

118
00:10:23,824 --> 00:10:26,727
How long's it been since you
been out in that visiting room?

119
00:10:26,827 --> 00:10:27,527
Not long.

120
00:10:31,098 --> 00:10:33,767
Five years.

121
00:10:33,867 --> 00:10:35,669
That's why we got to
get you out of here.

122
00:10:35,769 --> 00:10:39,272
We got to get you out of here.

123
00:10:39,372 --> 00:10:41,274
No, we don't gotta do nothing.

124
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:42,609
It ain't fair for
me to come back here

125
00:10:42,710 --> 00:10:43,576
Every time I want to see you.

126
00:10:43,677 --> 00:10:44,644
So don't come back!

127
00:10:44,745 --> 00:10:45,445
Try.

128
00:10:45,545 --> 00:10:47,347
For me?

129
00:10:47,447 --> 00:10:49,883
Outside the world
just comes down on me.

130
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:50,684
It doesn't let up.

131
00:10:50,784 --> 00:10:53,186
I can't.

132
00:10:53,286 --> 00:10:54,121
It's OK.

133
00:10:54,221 --> 00:10:55,055
No, it's not OK.

134
00:10:55,155 --> 00:10:56,423
I can't ask you
to come back here.

135
00:10:56,523 --> 00:10:57,357
I want to see you again.

136
00:10:57,457 --> 00:10:58,992
But I can't ask
you to come back.

137
00:11:02,095 --> 00:11:03,997
I'll come up once a week.

138
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:05,498
You better go.

139
00:11:23,050 --> 00:11:24,151
I'm gonna read up on it.

140
00:11:24,251 --> 00:11:24,952
What?

141
00:11:25,052 --> 00:11:27,620
Agoraphobia.

142
00:11:27,721 --> 00:11:29,089
Maybe someday I can help you.

143
00:11:32,325 --> 00:11:33,026
Cajun?

144
00:11:43,937 --> 00:11:44,838
Thanks for the guitar, man.

145
00:11:48,876 --> 00:11:52,245
Are you gonna play it?

146
00:11:52,345 --> 00:11:53,847
Just like when
I was a kid, huh?

147
00:11:58,418 --> 00:11:59,719
- Brothers.
- I'll play it.

148
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:00,520
That's enough.

149
00:12:28,916 --> 00:12:29,817
Hey, soldier.

150
00:12:29,917 --> 00:12:30,918
You all packed and
ready to go home?

151
00:12:33,954 --> 00:12:35,522
Yeah.

152
00:12:35,622 --> 00:12:36,656
Where'd you get the guitar?

153
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:38,458
I thought you sold yours.

154
00:12:38,558 --> 00:12:39,592
I did.

155
00:12:39,692 --> 00:12:41,328
Legs gave me this one.

156
00:12:41,428 --> 00:12:42,129
Come on.

157
00:12:42,229 --> 00:12:42,930
Car's downstairs.

158
00:13:12,025 --> 00:13:12,725
So?

159
00:13:15,562 --> 00:13:17,264
Where is he?

160
00:13:17,364 --> 00:13:19,332
Uh, word on the street is...

161
00:13:19,432 --> 00:13:21,034
I don't give a damn about
the word on the street.

162
00:13:21,134 --> 00:13:22,435
Where is he?

163
00:13:22,535 --> 00:13:23,803
Uh, h-he went west.

164
00:13:23,904 --> 00:13:24,804
Maybe California.

165
00:13:24,905 --> 00:13:26,739
Nah, I took him
out of VA hospital.

166
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:28,308
He's probably back there.

167
00:13:28,408 --> 00:13:29,943
Now, sit down.
Both of you.

168
00:13:33,513 --> 00:13:34,948
He was a machine.

169
00:13:35,048 --> 00:13:38,051
The best kickboxer I ever had.

170
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:39,953
Then he double-crossed me.

171
00:13:40,053 --> 00:13:43,423
So what do you
want us to do, boss?

172
00:13:43,523 --> 00:13:45,959
I'm gonna arrange
his last fight.

173
00:13:46,059 --> 00:13:48,461
H... h... he... he
won't fight no more.

174
00:13:48,561 --> 00:13:50,430
Oh, yes, he will.

175
00:13:54,434 --> 00:13:57,737
He's gonna fight.

176
00:13:57,837 --> 00:13:59,206
He's gonna fight.

177
00:14:02,242 --> 00:14:04,878
You find him.

178
00:14:04,978 --> 00:14:05,778
You call me.

179
00:14:21,661 --> 00:14:24,197
Lacy told me to tell you,
your old job's waiting for you.

180
00:14:28,201 --> 00:14:29,069
Hey.

181
00:14:29,169 --> 00:14:30,971
Play for me.

182
00:14:31,071 --> 00:14:33,140
You are gonna come back
to work, aren't you, Cage?

183
00:14:36,977 --> 00:14:37,677
I guess I will.

184
00:14:43,683 --> 00:14:47,720
Ali, I want to thank you for...
For being here when I need you.

185
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:48,521
How was your stay?

186
00:14:48,621 --> 00:14:49,322
Did they help?

187
00:14:51,858 --> 00:14:53,593
Them people don't understand...

188
00:14:53,693 --> 00:14:55,028
The dreams?

189
00:14:55,128 --> 00:14:56,129
No, hell.

190
00:14:56,229 --> 00:14:57,464
They don't understand
how to treat a vet.

191
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:00,600
I'm scared.

192
00:15:03,403 --> 00:15:05,472
They don't know scared.

193
00:15:05,572 --> 00:15:06,339
I know.

194
00:15:09,042 --> 00:15:11,278
Do you?

195
00:15:11,378 --> 00:15:13,346
Hey, just like the hospital,
I can be your friend too,

196
00:15:13,446 --> 00:15:14,214
You know.

197
00:15:14,314 --> 00:15:15,282
Yeah, it's easy for you.

198
00:15:15,382 --> 00:15:16,883
You know, you got
it all together.

199
00:15:16,984 --> 00:15:18,618
(LAUGHING) What?

200
00:15:18,718 --> 00:15:20,220
Oh, big deal.

201
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:24,591
So I sing and play at the club.

202
00:15:24,691 --> 00:15:25,392
I'm scared, too.

203
00:15:25,492 --> 00:15:27,094
But I'm not giving up.

204
00:15:27,194 --> 00:15:29,062
Hey, wait a minute.

205
00:15:29,162 --> 00:15:30,230
I'm not giving up.

206
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:32,799
Come on, just because my
mind's on other things

207
00:15:32,899 --> 00:15:34,401
Sometimes... I get caught
up in my own thoughts,

208
00:15:34,501 --> 00:15:44,011
And... I guess that is
kind of selfish, isn't it?

209
00:15:44,111 --> 00:15:44,811
It's all right.

210
00:15:44,911 --> 00:15:48,081
I do the same thing.

211
00:15:48,181 --> 00:15:50,417
Would you be there for me,
Cage, if I needed a friend?

212
00:16:01,761 --> 00:16:04,731
Hey, uh... tell me something.

213
00:16:04,831 --> 00:16:05,999
Who paid the rent
on my apartment

214
00:16:06,099 --> 00:16:07,500
While I was in the hospital?

215
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,335
None of your business.

216
00:16:08,435 --> 00:16:12,105
(PLAYING GUITAR)

217
00:16:12,205 --> 00:16:23,783
(SINGING) I L-U-V Y-O-U. I
need you B-A-D, oh, baby, I do.

218
00:16:23,883 --> 00:16:26,986
I'm in L-U-V with Y-O-U.

219
00:16:27,087 --> 00:16:28,921
[Crowd cheering]

220
00:16:29,022 --> 00:16:38,598
(SINGING) I L-U-V Y-O-U. I
need you B-A-D, oh, baby, I do.

221
00:16:38,698 --> 00:16:46,206
I'm in L-U-V with Y-O-U. I
quit school when I was 12.

222
00:16:46,306 --> 00:16:48,675
I can't read or write too well.

223
00:16:48,775 --> 00:16:54,147
Singing songs is
one thing I can do.

224
00:16:54,247 --> 00:16:58,585
I sing the words
I wrote for you.

225
00:16:58,685 --> 00:17:08,995
I L-U-V Y-O-U. I need you
B-A-D, oh, baby, I do.

226
00:17:09,096 --> 00:17:17,270
I'm in L-U-V with Y-O-U.
I'm in L-U-V with Y-O-U.

227
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:18,871
She sounds good tonight.

228
00:17:18,971 --> 00:17:19,772
Boy, she's great.

229
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:27,114
So you guys, I, uh... I
hadn't said anything before.

230
00:17:27,214 --> 00:17:30,883
But I just want to
tell you... thanks.

231
00:17:30,983 --> 00:17:31,918
Yeah.

232
00:17:32,018 --> 00:17:34,721
We're all glad to
have you back, Cage.

233
00:17:34,821 --> 00:17:37,090
Even though your friend
Pedro, here, saved

234
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:39,058
All the hard ones for you.

235
00:17:45,031 --> 00:17:55,442
(SINGING) I'm in L-U-V with
Y-O-U. I'm in L-U-V with Y-O-U.

236
00:17:55,542 --> 00:18:02,849
I'm in L-U-V with Y-O-U.

237
00:18:02,949 --> 00:18:04,351
All right.

238
00:18:04,451 --> 00:18:05,818
Thank you.

239
00:18:05,918 --> 00:18:07,787
Thank you very much.

240
00:18:07,887 --> 00:18:10,757
All right, here's Rif Harper.

241
00:18:10,857 --> 00:18:13,226
[Crowd cheering]

242
00:18:18,265 --> 00:18:21,634
(SINGING) Said you really
want to want somebody.

243
00:18:21,734 --> 00:18:25,071
That's what you said.

244
00:18:25,172 --> 00:18:29,509
Well, if you really want to want
somebody, why'd you run away?

245
00:18:29,609 --> 00:18:32,279
Why'd you run away?

246
00:18:32,379 --> 00:18:34,914
Guys, have you finished
shredding the cabbage yet?

247
00:18:35,014 --> 00:18:37,884
I only got two hands.

248
00:18:37,984 --> 00:18:39,519
All right.

249
00:18:39,619 --> 00:18:40,520
Go ahead.

250
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:41,688
Make my coleslaw.

251
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:46,959
Hey, Cage.

252
00:18:47,059 --> 00:18:48,295
How you feeling?

253
00:18:48,395 --> 00:18:50,197
Just feels good to
have a job, Pedro.

254
00:18:50,297 --> 00:18:51,398
That's cool.

255
00:18:51,498 --> 00:18:53,166
You should have [inaudible]
more often, you see?

256
00:18:53,266 --> 00:18:54,867
Just like me.

257
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:56,169
I love this place.

258
00:18:56,269 --> 00:18:57,504
I love even these turkeys.

259
00:18:57,604 --> 00:18:59,272
You see, I love cooking.

260
00:18:59,372 --> 00:19:00,440
You wash them up.

261
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:02,442
And I mess them
up with more food!

262
00:19:02,542 --> 00:19:05,178
Enjoy.

263
00:19:05,278 --> 00:19:06,979
Pedro, where's the gravy?

264
00:19:07,079 --> 00:19:09,949
Since when do we put gravy
on ham and hash browns, huh?

