00:56:45,302 --> 00:56:46,070
You did there.

798
00:56:48,739 --> 00:56:51,275
I keep fight no
more, Mr. Regetti.

799
00:56:51,375 --> 00:56:53,343
Look, why don't you boys
just leave me alone, huh?

800
00:56:56,814 --> 00:56:59,149
Come here.

801
00:56:59,249 --> 00:57:00,618
It's money.

802
00:57:00,718 --> 00:57:01,452
Hm?

803
00:57:01,552 --> 00:57:03,621
You understand money?

804
00:57:03,721 --> 00:57:06,423
I arranged a very
special fight for you.

805
00:57:06,524 --> 00:57:07,658
And you're the star attraction.

806
00:57:10,327 --> 00:57:12,730
Ain't gonna be much of a fight.

807
00:57:12,830 --> 00:57:14,565
Get him up.

808
00:57:14,665 --> 00:57:18,368
I'm through fighting, damn it.

809
00:57:18,469 --> 00:57:19,870
[Phone ringing]

810
00:57:24,441 --> 00:57:26,043
Hello?

811
00:57:26,143 --> 00:57:29,313
Oh, hi, Lacy.

812
00:57:29,413 --> 00:57:30,781
Oh, sure.

813
00:57:30,881 --> 00:57:32,517
Why do you want to
see me so early?

814
00:57:35,486 --> 00:57:36,186
All right.

815
00:57:36,286 --> 00:57:37,855
I'll be right down.

816
00:57:37,955 --> 00:57:39,890
Bye.

817
00:57:39,990 --> 00:57:42,560
All I want you to
do is think it over.

818
00:57:42,660 --> 00:57:43,360
OK?

819
00:57:43,460 --> 00:57:46,330
Think it over.

820
00:57:46,430 --> 00:57:47,364
I don't need to.

821
00:57:47,464 --> 00:57:48,232
I've thought about it.

822
00:57:48,332 --> 00:57:49,033
OK.

823
00:57:49,133 --> 00:57:50,400
Take your time.

824
00:57:50,501 --> 00:57:53,604
I'll give you a couple days.

825
00:57:53,704 --> 00:57:55,105
I'll come back tomorrow.

826
00:57:55,205 --> 00:57:57,241
And we'll discuss the details.

827
00:57:59,877 --> 00:58:00,578
Mr. Regetti.

828
00:58:04,515 --> 00:58:05,983
What happens if I
don't change my mind?

829
00:58:11,455 --> 00:58:14,358
I'm going to kill you.

830
00:58:14,458 --> 00:58:16,160
Hm.

831
00:58:16,260 --> 00:58:17,461
Anyways, so because of the, uh...

832
00:58:17,562 --> 00:58:18,428
Great.

833
00:58:18,529 --> 00:58:19,496
Is it?

834
00:58:19,597 --> 00:58:20,898
Honey, because of the
fire at The Palace

835
00:58:20,998 --> 00:58:24,068
I offered the stars our place
for them to hold their concert.

836
00:58:24,168 --> 00:58:25,435
And they said yes.

837
00:58:25,536 --> 00:58:26,236
Great!

838
00:58:28,973 --> 00:58:32,476
And that includes you.

839
00:58:32,577 --> 00:58:33,578
Thanks, Lacy.

840
00:58:33,678 --> 00:58:35,112
But I hardly think I'd
be acceptable to all

841
00:58:35,212 --> 00:58:36,981
Those big stars.

842
00:58:37,081 --> 00:58:39,216
Well, you know, when
Rif Harper saw your work,

843
00:58:39,316 --> 00:58:40,184
He loved what you did.

844
00:58:40,284 --> 00:58:41,251
And he told the others about it.

845
00:58:41,351 --> 00:58:42,052
And they all said yes.

846
00:58:42,152 --> 00:58:43,888
They give their approval.

847
00:58:43,988 --> 00:58:45,890
Where would I fit
into a show like this?

848
00:58:45,990 --> 00:58:47,191
Right smack in the middle.

849
00:58:47,291 --> 00:58:48,793
Ali, this is wonderful.

850
00:58:48,893 --> 00:58:52,897
I can't think of a better
showcase for your talents.

851
00:58:52,997 --> 00:58:54,498
All right!

852
00:58:54,599 --> 00:58:55,766
Now, look.
You.

853
00:58:55,866 --> 00:58:56,567
Get out of here.

854
00:58:56,667 --> 00:58:57,367
Go home.

855
00:58:57,467 --> 00:58:58,703
Do anything you want to do.

856
00:58:58,803 --> 00:59:03,107
But please, please be on time.

857
00:59:03,207 --> 00:59:04,609
Hey, I'm always on time.

858
00:59:16,821 --> 00:59:17,521
Ali.

859
00:59:17,622 --> 00:59:19,690
Don't turn around.

860
00:59:19,790 --> 00:59:22,226
Look, just act normal, baby.

861
00:59:22,326 --> 00:59:23,527
What's wrong?

862
00:59:23,628 --> 00:59:26,296
Just start the car up, drive
off, and go to the beach.

863
00:59:26,396 --> 00:59:27,297
But stay away from my place.

864
00:59:27,397 --> 00:59:28,098
Come on.

865
00:59:28,198 --> 00:59:28,966
Do it.

866
00:59:40,645 --> 00:59:41,511
All right.

867
00:59:41,612 --> 00:59:42,346
Nobody followed us.

868
00:59:42,446 --> 00:59:43,948
What in the world is going on?

869
00:59:44,048 --> 00:59:47,217
Just stay away from my place.

870
00:59:47,317 --> 00:59:49,086
Thank God they don't
know where you live.

871
00:59:49,186 --> 00:59:50,287
Are you trying to scare me?

872
00:59:50,387 --> 00:59:51,889
No, I'm trying to educate you.

873
00:59:51,989 --> 00:59:53,023
Listen to me.

874
00:59:53,123 --> 00:59:56,426
Six months ago, I was a
kickboxer in New York.

875
00:59:56,526 --> 00:59:57,527
What?

876
00:59:57,628 --> 00:59:59,263
There's a guy who's
into organized crime.

877
00:59:59,363 --> 01:00:03,133
He owns my contract.

878
01:00:03,233 --> 01:00:05,636
He lost a lot of money on me.

879
01:00:05,736 --> 01:00:08,272
Well, he's come to get it back.

880
01:00:08,372 --> 01:00:09,273
But you don't have any money.

881
01:00:09,373 --> 01:00:12,242
He wants me to fight again.

882
01:00:12,342 --> 01:00:15,379
It's a special event.

883
01:00:15,479 --> 01:00:17,447
It's a fight to the death.

884
01:00:17,547 --> 01:00:19,349
Then lets go to the police.

885
01:00:19,449 --> 01:00:20,384
No!

886
01:00:20,484 --> 01:00:21,752
Now, you listen to me.

887
01:00:21,852 --> 01:00:23,921
I want you to get up there
on that stage tomorrow

888
01:00:24,021 --> 01:00:26,190
Night and knock 'em dead.

889
01:00:26,290 --> 01:00:28,959
You're gonna shine
like a star, baby.

890
01:00:29,059 --> 01:00:30,460
It's been your lifetime goal.

891
01:00:30,560 --> 01:00:31,428
Come on.

892
01:00:31,528 --> 01:00:32,496
It's not that important.

893
01:00:32,596 --> 01:00:34,699
It is that important.

894
01:00:34,799 --> 01:00:36,600
I've gotten away from
these guys before.

895
01:00:36,701 --> 01:00:37,567
And I'll do it again.

896
01:00:40,570 --> 01:00:43,808
Besides, I'm supposed to
be pursuing you, remember?

897
01:00:43,908 --> 01:00:46,076
You sure have a
funny way of doing it.

898
01:00:49,980 --> 01:00:52,282
I ain't gonna let you go.

899
01:00:52,382 --> 01:00:53,984
You know I'm coming back, baby.

900
01:01:37,261 --> 01:01:39,429
Who's here?

901
01:01:39,529 --> 01:01:40,898
What do you want?

902
01:01:45,970 --> 01:01:48,572
(SCREAMS)

903
01:01:48,672 --> 01:01:49,373
[Inaudible].

904
01:02:46,630 --> 01:02:49,566
(WHISPERING) Legs.

905
01:02:49,666 --> 01:02:50,367
Legs.

906
01:02:53,403 --> 01:02:58,742
Shh shh shh shh shh shh.

907
01:02:58,843 --> 01:03:00,210
You outta your... you crazy?

908
01:03:00,310 --> 01:03:02,212
Maybe.

909
01:03:02,312 --> 01:03:03,180
What's going on.

910
01:03:06,350 --> 01:03:07,384
Regetti's back.

911
01:03:07,484 --> 01:03:08,886
Oh, shit.

912
01:03:08,986 --> 01:03:12,356
He wants me for a
fight to the death.

913
01:03:12,456 --> 01:03:13,523
Listen to me.

914
01:03:13,623 --> 01:03:15,625
I need your help, man.

915
01:03:15,725 --> 01:03:16,793
I need to disappear for a while.

916
01:03:19,563 --> 01:03:21,698
OK?

917
01:03:21,798 --> 01:03:24,568
So what about Ali?

918
01:03:24,668 --> 01:03:26,136
She's playing this
big show at the club.

919
01:03:29,673 --> 01:03:30,440
Buddy Ray Lester.

920
01:03:30,540 --> 01:03:31,241
We'll give him a call.

921
01:03:31,341 --> 01:03:33,043
He can put you up tonight.

922
01:03:33,143 --> 01:03:35,645
And he'll take care of things.

923
01:03:35,745 --> 01:03:37,714
So when's this fight
supposed take place?

924
01:03:37,814 --> 01:03:39,917
Tomorrow night.

925
01:03:40,017 --> 01:03:40,918
Oh, man.

926
01:03:41,018 --> 01:03:42,386
You're nuts.

927
01:03:42,486 --> 01:03:44,354
Don't tell me.

928
01:03:44,454 --> 01:03:46,924
You want to go see her, right?

929
01:03:47,024 --> 01:03:49,059
I've got to see her, man.

930
01:03:49,159 --> 01:03:51,061
I mean, she's waited for
this all of her life.

931
01:03:51,161 --> 01:03:53,730
This is her big chance.

932
01:03:53,830 --> 01:03:56,466
I wish you could see her, Legs.

933
01:03:56,566 --> 01:03:57,868
Hey, I'm... I'm
working on just trying

934
01:03:57,968 --> 01:04:00,470
To get my ass off this floor...
Not out of the whole building.

935
01:04:00,570 --> 01:04:02,907
Legs, if I don't
fight, they'll kill me.

936
01:04:03,007 --> 01:04:05,910
What's worse is
they might hurt Ali.

937
01:04:06,010 --> 01:04:07,611
I ain't had a fight
in six months, man.

938
01:04:07,711 --> 01:04:10,247
I'm out of shape.

939
01:04:10,347 --> 01:04:11,815
Either way, I'll lose.

940
01:04:11,916 --> 01:04:13,617
Take your old lady and get
your ass out of town, man.

941
01:04:13,717 --> 01:04:15,285
I don't need you
to babysit my ass.

942
01:04:15,385 --> 01:04:16,386
Go.
Thanks, buddy.

943
01:04:16,486 --> 01:04:17,187
Thanks.

944
01:04:19,990 --> 01:04:20,690
Tell us.

945
01:04:24,061 --> 01:04:26,496
I'll find out where he is, boss.

946
01:04:26,596 --> 01:04:28,865
Eh... eh... eh, that's enough.

947
01:04:28,966 --> 01:04:30,834
Leave her alone.

948
01:04:30,935 --> 01:04:33,170
You going to tell
us where he is?

949
01:04:33,270 --> 01:04:35,772
I told you, I don't
know where he is.

950
01:04:35,872 --> 01:04:37,574
He's got to fight.

951
01:04:37,674 --> 01:04:39,076
Why don't you just
leave him alone?

952
01:04:39,176 --> 01:04:41,045
Well, I got a...
Some of my friends

953
01:04:41,145 --> 01:04:43,313
Are gonna get together
tomorrow night.

954
01:04:43,413 --> 01:04:45,815
They're expecting
to see a fight.

955
01:04:45,916 --> 01:04:48,152
They bet an awful lot
of money on this fight.

956
01:04:48,252 --> 01:04:51,121
And your Cage is the
feature attraction.

957
01:04:51,221 --> 01:04:52,456
If he don't want to
fight, they're going

958
01:04:52,556 --> 01:04:54,358
To lose an awful lot of money.

959
01:04:54,458 --> 01:04:56,893
My friends are going
to be very unhappy.

960
01:04:56,994 --> 01:04:57,694
I told you.

961
01:04:57,794 --> 01:04:59,829
I don't know where he is.

962
01:04:59,930 --> 01:05:01,865
You play the guitar,
don't you, honey?

963
01:05:01,966 --> 01:05:03,567
Yeah.

964
01:05:03,667 --> 01:05:06,070
Wouldn't it be awful if
you couldn't play anymore?

965
01:05:06,170 --> 01:05:07,371
What do you mean?

966
01:05:11,608 --> 01:05:12,943
Put her hand in the vice.

967
01:05:13,043 --> 01:05:15,279
Maybe she can
remember where he is.

968
01:05:15,379 --> 01:05:17,247
No!

969
01:05:17,347 --> 01:05:18,715
No... [screams]

970
01:05:18,815 --> 01:05:22,352
[Music playing]

971
01:05:41,571 --> 01:05:42,772
TOMMY ROE (SINGING):
Don't let me down.

972
01:05:47,444 --> 01:05:48,245
Well, Lacy.

973
01:05:48,345 --> 01:05:50,314
How'd we sound?

974
01:05:50,414 --> 01:05:51,381
You sound terrific!

975
01:05:51,481 --> 01:05:53,083
What a sound.

976
01:05:53,183 --> 01:05:54,318
Pedro.

977
01:05:54,418 --> 01:05:55,519
Listen... have you seen Ali?

978
01:05:55,619 --> 01:05:57,221
No, not tonight, bro.

979
01:05:57,321 --> 01:05:58,722
I don't think she's come in yet.

980
01:05:58,822 --> 01:05:59,756
No, she's got to be here, man.

981
01:05:59,856 --> 01:06:01,158
Sh... she ain't never late.

982
01:06:01,258 --> 01:06:02,926
Hey, why don't you
go and ask Lacy.

983
01:06:07,697 --> 01:06:09,166
You know, Rif was telling
us about this place.

984
01:06:09,266 --> 01:06:10,467
It's really fantastic.

985
01:06:10,567 --> 01:06:12,602
Hey, Lacy, have you seen Ali?

986
01:06:12,702 --> 01:06:14,138
No, she's probably
having her hair

987
01:06:14,238 --> 01:06:15,205
Done or something like that.

988
01:06:15,305 --> 01:06:16,540
I mean, she should
have been here by now.

989
01:06:16,640 --> 01:06:18,775
Isn't her rehearsal next?

990
01:06:18,875 --> 01:06:21,378
Maybe she had trouble
getting here, or... Cage.

991
01:06:21,478 --> 01:06:22,646
What the hell's happening?

992
01:06:22,746 --> 01:06:23,580
Nothing.

993
01:06:23,680 --> 01:06:24,381
Hey, listen.

994
01:06:24,481 --> 01:06:27,051
Is there anything we can do?

995
01:06:27,151 --> 01:06:28,052
No, thanks.

996
01:06:48,972 --> 01:06:50,507
Where is he?

997
01:06:50,607 --> 01:06:52,242
She doesn't know.

998
01:06:52,342 --> 01:06:54,944
She would have told us.

999
01:06:55,045 --> 01:06:58,282
What do you want us to do.

1000
01:06:58,382 --> 01:06:59,749
Lock her up.

1001
01:06:59,849 --> 01:07:00,617
Watch both apartments.

1002
01:07:03,687 --> 01:07:07,291
When he realizes
she's not around,

1003
01:07:07,391 --> 01:07:10,527
He'll go to one or the other.

1004
01:07:10,627 --> 01:07:11,328
Shit.

1005
01:07:14,231 --> 01:07:15,365
The fight starts at 6 o'clock.

1006
01:07:15,465 --> 01:07:16,233
We don't want to be late.

1007
01:07:53,870 --> 01:07:54,571
Damn.

1008
01:08:02,146 --> 01:08:04,548
I'll pull the
trigger, if I have to.

1009
01:08:10,187 --> 01:08:11,521
Where's Ali, Lou.

1010
01:08:11,621 --> 01:08:13,957
We got her, Cage.

1011
01:08:14,057 --> 01:08:15,792
We roughed her up a bit.

1012
01:08:15,892 --> 01:08:19,329
I got her waiting for
you at the fights.

1013
01:08:19,429 --> 01:08:20,697
Great for coming out tonight.

1014
01:08:33,009 --> 01:08:35,479
(SINGING) Staring
out the window

1015
01:08:35,579 --> 01:08:38,615
At the raindrops pouring down.

1016
01:08:38,715 --> 01:08:43,520
Takes me to another
time and place.

1017
01:08:43,620 --> 01:08:49,493
I had more hair on my head
then, and less lines on my face.

1018
01:08:49,593 --> 01:08:54,298
And I didn't have this
spare tire round my waist.

1019
01:08:54,398 --> 01:08:55,732
I'm glad you came
to your senses.

1020
01:09:00,704 --> 01:09:01,405
Where is Ali?

1021
01:09:04,374 --> 01:09:07,411
She's my insurance.

1022
01:09:07,511 --> 01:09:11,114
Sort of a guarantee
that you'll fight.

1023
01:09:11,215 --> 01:09:14,150
(SINGING) Turned round,
saw your hair was brown.

1024
01:09:14,251 --> 01:09:16,586
Last night you was
a blonde, I swore.

1025
01:09:16,686 --> 01:09:21,558
But my head was so bad, I was
looking just to make a score.

1026
01:09:21,658 --> 01:09:23,893
She ain't Johnnie.

1027
01:09:23,993 --> 01:09:26,863
She ain't bad.

1028
01:09:26,963 --> 01:09:32,336
She ain't the best
thing I ever had.

1029
01:09:32,436 --> 01:09:37,274
Last night she kept
me from feeling sad.

1030
01:09:37,374 --> 01:09:40,777
She ain't Johnnie.

1031
01:09:40,877 --> 01:09:44,248
But she ain't bad.

1032
01:09:44,348 --> 01:09:49,953
Just in case you do something
stupid, she'll pay for it.

1033
01:09:50,053 --> 01:09:50,754
OK?

1034
01:10:00,163 --> 01:10:01,265
Let's get this over with.

1035
01:10:01,365 --> 01:10:04,634
(SINGING) Met a green-eyed
lady from Oklahoma City

1036
01:10:04,734 --> 01:10:07,371
With a tattoo of butterfly.

1037
01:10:07,471 --> 01:10:09,539
She was hotter
than a firecracker

1038
01:10:09,639 --> 01:10:13,076
On the Fourth of July.

1039
01:10:13,176 --> 01:10:16,546
I kissed her on the lips,
then I kissed her shoulder.

1040
01:10:16,646 --> 01:10:18,014
Then I kissed her
on the butterfly.

1041
01:10:18,114 --> 01:10:20,350
I waited till she
closed her eyes

1042
01:10:20,450 --> 01:10:24,153
And then I kissed her goodbye.

1043
01:10:24,254 --> 01:10:26,055
She ain't Johnnie.

1044
01:10:26,155 --> 01:10:28,492
But she ain't bad.

1045
01:10:28,592 --> 01:10:34,964
She ain't the best
thing I ever had.

1046
01:10:35,064 --> 01:10:40,404
That night she kept
me from feeling sad.

1047
01:10:40,504 --> 01:10:46,376
She ain't Johnnie,
but she ain't bad.

1048
01:10:46,476 --> 01:10:50,814
So here I stand just like
a sneaking, peeping tom.

1049
01:10:50,914 --> 01:10:52,816
Peepin' over the back fence.

1050
01:10:52,916 --> 01:10:56,286
You've got to see what
Johnnie's [inaudible].

1051
01:10:56,386 --> 01:10:58,755
She's hanging clothes.

1052
01:10:58,855 --> 01:11:02,225
And though there's
curlers in her hair

1053
01:11:02,326 --> 01:11:06,763
There's still a trace
of my Johnnie there.

1054
01:11:06,863 --> 01:11:09,599
She ain't Johnnie.

1055
01:11:09,699 --> 01:11:12,336
But she ain't bad.

1056
01:11:12,436 --> 01:11:18,141
She's still the best
thing I ever had.

1057
01:11:18,241 --> 01:11:24,013
And coming back here
just makes me sad.

1058
01:11:24,113 --> 01:11:26,516
She ain't Johnnie.

1059
01:11:26,616 --> 01:11:28,184
But she ain't bad.

1060
01:11:35,792 --> 01:11:37,160
[Bell ringing]

1061
01:11:37,260 --> 01:11:39,128
Everybody having a good time?

1062
01:11:39,228 --> 01:11:40,296
[Cheering]

1063
01:11:40,397 --> 01:11:41,230
Great.

